## Audit & Recommendation Policy

When the user requests audits or recommendations:
- **Acknowledge when the app is polished.** If the codebase is in good shape, say so clearly. Don't invent issues to fill a report.
- **Avoid circular or unnecessary recommendations.** Don't recommend changes that add little value, introduce risk, or churn for its own sake.
- **Avoid destructive recommendations.** Prefer incremental, low-risk improvements. Flag breaking changes or high-effort refactors only when they solve real problems.
